{
  "text": "At least some protists were living in normoxic and halocline DHAB sediments, as evidenced by positive CellTracker Green labeling along with DAPI analysis indicating the lack of associated microbes but the presence of a nucleus or nuclei (e.g., Figure 8) . Importantly, we do not assert positive DAPI staining indicates viability, as we are aware that DNA can be preserved in DHAB brines (e.g., [CITATION_1] . Regardless, at least some protists lacking prokaryotic associates appear to inhabit upper, mid-, and lower DHAB halocline sediments.",
